 lid, heat <b>20 min\/120°C\/speed 1<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside to cool. Clean mixing bowl."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Fishcakes"},{"content":"Place coriander in mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 8<b>. Add chilli, ginger and garlic then chop <b>3 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add spring onions, lime zest, soy sauce, sesame oil, cornflour, cumin and palm sugar then mix <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>."},{"content":"Add fish and prawns then chop <b>3 sec\/speed 5<b>."},{"content":"Shape mixture into 12 balls then flatten into fish cakes. Transfer to a plate, cover with cling film, and place in fridge to chill for 30 minutes."},{"content":"Preheat oven to 200°C and line a baking tray with baking paper."},{"content":"Place water and salt in mixing bowl then insert simmering basket. Weigh rice into simmering basket and cook <b>35 min\/Varoma\/speed 3.5<b>. Meanwhile, continue with recipe."},{"content":"Place fish cakes on prepared baking tray and bake 25-30 minutes (200°C) until golden brown."},{"content":"To serve, divide rice between 4 plates, place 3 fish cakes on each, and serve with dipping sauce."}],"basicInfo":["medium","15m","1h 40m","4 portions"]}